Devendor libpg_query: build pglast against the system (conda) libpg_query
package instead of the bundled git submodule.

This mirrors Debian's `libpq-query` patch (debian/patches in the pglast source
package): the two internal headers move under the installed `pg_query/`
directory, and setup.py's custom build_ext that compiles the bundled
libpg_query via `make` is dropped. The remaining external headers resolve from
the conda prefix at build time:
  - pg_query.h, pg_query/pg_query_internal.h, pg_query/pg_query.pb-c.h  -> libpg_query
  - postgres.h, nodes/*.h (via -I$PREFIX/include/pg_query/postgres)     -> libpg_query
  - protobuf-c/protobuf-c.h                                             -> protobuf-c

The committed pglast/parser.c is regenerated from this patched parser.pyx
during the build (see build.sh) so the new include paths take effect.
